On The Bachelorette, Dave was the next to go, being dumped by Sam. Courtesy: Network Ten October 14th 2015 21 hours ago /video/video.news.com.au/Entertainment/ 
AFTER each episode, we ask The Bachelorette’s host to answer five of our burning questions about the show. 
Read on for Osher Gunsberg’s take on the re-emergence of Sasha as frontrunner, Dave’s awkward departure and what to expect on the hometown visits tonight. Fact finding mission ... Whether they were fun, interesting or sad, Sam Frost was taken with the boys’ facts. Caught in the act ... The boys were casually working out when Osher arrived with the date card. Real artist ... Sasha and Sam created an epic chemistry masterpiece on their date. Awkward moments ... Dave struggled at the final five dinner. A word of advice ... Did Warwick (left) clue in the families on how to grill Sam Frost? 1 of n 
1. First and most importantly. In your opinion, what is the difference between a fun fact, an interesting fact and a sad fact? 
“That’s a very difficult question to answer because it all very much depends on what you have as your reaction. If you know, when you are writing a fact down that Sam’s going to read it and have to guess who wrote it, that’s an opportunity to form some sort of connection. When Michael wrote, ‘I’m afraid I won’t find love,’ yeah, not exactly fun, not exactly interesting, most definitely excellent. Well played.”
